      "content": "okay, i see. so if you look at the historical data from previous reform cycles, is there actually any empirical evidence that \"trickle-down\" effects work, or is the consensus more on the side that it's just a tool for wealth concentration? like, if i were writing my conclusion, which perspective is backed by more actual economic data?",
